&lt;li&gt;Translate the CEO&#39;s and Chief of Staff&#39;s priorities into structured workplans, timelines, and clear next steps; eliminate ambiguity so the right work happens fast.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare materials for executive meetings, board interactions, and investor touchpoints, including briefing notes, agendas, decks, data summaries, and post-meeting action trackers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct quick-turn analysis and research on business, market, regulatory, and operational questions; deliver crisp, decision-ready synthesis, not raw data dumps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain automation and AI-enabled workflows that scale the productivity of the Office of the CEO; if it can be automated, automate it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track progress on OKRs, strategic initiatives, and executive commitments across functions; surface blockers and risks early, with proposed solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with leaders across Engineering, Product, Finance, People, Legal, and Marketing to keep executive priorities moving in parallel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a trusted, discreet extension of executive leadership; handle confidential information with absolute integrity.&lt;/li&gt;
